    • find

      public TeamList.TeamNode find(String teamID)
      A method called find(), which accepts one parameter of type String representing a teamID. Method then searches the list for a teamNode with that teamID. If such an object is found, then method returns a pointer to that teamNode; otherwise, method returns null. The method must keep track of how many iterations were made before the search finally finds the team or concludes that it is not in the list.
      Parameters:
      teamID - the ID of the team to be returned
      Returns:
      the node in the list with the given teamID and null if not found This method can cause privacy leaks
